<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<listitem id="components.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.enterpriseBeans.sessionBeans.stateless.exercises.adderStatelessSessionBean">
  <para>
    Write a stateless session bean, <literal>Adder</literal>, which
    receives 2 numbers and returns the sum of these. You may want to 
    follow the following steps: 
    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Write the remote interface </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Write the home interface </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Write a bean implementation class </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Write a the generic and JBoss-specific XML deployment descriptors (i.e. the
            <literal>ejb-jar.xml</literal> and  
          <literal>jboss.xml</literal> files). </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Write a Java client application. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Write an Ant build file with <literal>compile</literal>,
            <literal>archive</literal>,  
          <literal>deploy</literal>,  
          <literal>archiveClient</literal> and  
          <literal>runClient</literal> targets. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Generate the server and client archives and check the archive contents. In
          particular, check that the server side jar contents and structure is correct, i.e.
          that the <literal>ejb-jar.xml</literal> and  
          <literal>jboss.xml</literal> files are in a  
          <literal>/META-INF</literal> directory and that the classes are in the
          correct directories according to the packaging structure. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Start the JBoss application server. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Deploy the server side Jar file. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Correct any reported errors and redeploy. </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Run the client application.</para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
   </para> 
</listitem>
